&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;link href=&quot;https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;well&quot;&gt;
       &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
         &lt;input/&gt;
       &lt;/div&gt;
       &lt;div class=&quot;mb-0 form-group&quot;&gt;
         &lt;input/&gt;
       &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;well&quot;&gt;
       &lt;div class=&quot;form-group&quot;&gt;
         &lt;input/&gt;
       &lt;/div&gt;
       &lt;div class=&quot;mb-0 form-group&quot;&gt;
         &lt;input/&gt;
       &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

More on `mb-0`: [What is class=“mb-0” in Bootstrap 4?](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41574776/what-is-class-mb-0-in-bootstrap-4?noredirect=1)

If you don&#39;t want to add a class, You can also do this directly with the `:last-child` selector.

    .well .form-group:last-child {
         margin-bottom: 0!important;
    
    }

You can Use `&gt;` to specify the next child of `.well` of type `div`

`.well &gt; div.form-group:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
}`

